Source: gnome-twitch
Section: video
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Tim Dengel <tim.dengel.debian@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper, meson, libgtk-3-dev (>= 3.20), libpeas-dev, libsoup2.4-dev, libjson-glib-dev, libgstreamer1.0-dev, libclutter-gst-3.0-dev, libclutter-gtk-1.0-dev, libwebkit2gtk-4.0-dev, libmpv-dev
Standards-Version: 4.1.4.1
Homepage: https://github.com/vinszent/gnome-twitch
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/dengelt/gnome-twitch.git -b debian/sid
Vcs-Browser: https://github.com/dengelt/gnome-twitch/tree/debian/sid

Package: gnome-twitch
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: gnome-twitch-player-backend-gstreamer-cairo (= ${binary:Version}) | gnome-twitch-player-backend-gstreamer-opengl (= ${binary:Version}) | gnome-twitch-player-backend-gstreamer-clutter (= ${binary:Version}) | gnome-twitch-player-backend-mpv-opengl (= ${binary:Version})
Description: GNOME Twitch app for watching Twitch.tv streams without a browser or flash
 gnome-twitch provides a GTK3 interface for viewing streams on Twitch.
 At the moment you can
  * browse popular streams,
  * browse streams by game,
  * search for streams,
  * view streams,
  * use the chat with a Twitch account,
  * change the video quality,
  * follow streams on your Twitch account and
  * switch between player backends.
 More features like recording streams, VODs (Video-On-Demand),
 integration of Twitch account features
 like following streams are planned.

Package: gnome-twitch-player-backend-gstreamer-cairo
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, gstreamer1.0-libav, gstreamer1.0-plugins-base, gstreamer1.0-plugins-good, gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad, gnome-twitch (= ${binary:Version})
Description: Player backend for GNOME Twitch based on gstreamer+cairo
 Player backends are responsible for playing the actual video streams.
 Different player backends use different libraries to do this.
 This player backend uses GStreamer and cairo.

